"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Scottish: occupational name for a craftsman or maker of machinery, mostly in wood, of any of a wide range of kinds, from Middle English and Older Scots <i>wriht</i>, <i>wright</i>, <i>wricht</i>, <i>writh</i>, <i>write</i> (Old English <i>wyrhta</i>, <i>wryhta</i>) ‘craftsman’, especially ‘carpenter, joiner’. The term is found in various combinations (for example,   Cartwright   and   Wainwright  ), but when used in isolation it often referred to a builder of windmills or watermills. This surname is also very common among African Americans."],"variants":[{"name":"Wrights","meanings":["(1997: 103;2007: 204; 2010: NA)","English: variant of   Wright  , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."]},{"name":"Wrightsman","meanings":["Probably English (although no longer found in Britain), meaning‘servant of the wright’ (see   Wright  )."]},{"name":"Cartwright","meanings":["English (Midlands and northern England): occupational name from Middle English <i>cart(e)</i> ‘cart’ + <i>wright(e)</i> ‘craftsman’ (Old English <i>cræt</i> or Old Norse <i>kartr</i> + Old English <i>wyrhta</i>), for a cartwright, a maker of carts.","Variant of   Courtright  , a surname of Dutch origin."]},{"name":"Wrightson","meanings":["English (northern England, especially Durham): patronymic from   Wright  , meaning ‘son of the wright’."]},{"name":"Right","meanings":["(2007: 493; 2010: NA)","English: variant of   Wright  ."]},{"name":"McWright","meanings":["Scottish or Irish: Gaelic patronymic with the English and Scots occupational term   Wright  , meaning ‘son of the wright’. The name is possibly a part translation of   McIntyre  , which fully translates as ‘son of the wright’."]},{"name":"Wrightman","meanings":["English: occupational name from Middle English <i>wright</i> ‘craftsman’ (see   Wright  ) + <i>man</i> ‘man’, denoting someone who assisted a craftsman."]}]},{"name":"Mary","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Latin <i>Maria</i> via Old Welsh <i>Meir</i>.  See  <b>Mary</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mary Wright was born in 1482, in Wortham, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with John Betts."},"et":{"1482–":"1482–Surnud","1480–1550":"1480–1550","1508–1575":"1508–1575","1482–Female":"1482–Surnud","11 January 1508":"11. jaanuar 1508","1575":"1575","1550":"1550","1482":"1482","1508":"1508","1480":"1480","Of Wortham, Suffolk, England":"Wortham, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Wortham, Suffolk, England":"Wortham, Suffolk, England"},"fi":{"1482–":"1482–Kuollut","1480–1550":"1480–1550","1508–1575":"1508–1575","1482–Female":"1482–Kuollut","11 January 1508":"11. tammikuuta 1508","1575":"1575","1550":"1550","1482":"1482","1508":"1508","1480":"1480","Of Wortham, Suffolk, England":"Wortham, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Wortham, Suffolk, England":"Wortham, Suffolk, England"},"fr":{"1482–":"1482–Décédée","1480–1550":"1480–1550","1508–1575":"1508–1575","1482–Female":"1482–Décédée","11 January 1508":"11 janvier 1508","1575":"1575","1550":"1550","1482":"1482","1508":"1508","1480":"1480","Of Wortham, Suffolk, England":"Wortham, Suffolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Wortham, Suffolk, England":"Wortham, Suffolk, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Mary Wright est née en 1482, à Wortham, Suffolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec John Betts."},"de":{"1482–":"1482–Verstorben","1480–1550":"1480–1550","1508–1575":"1508–1575","1482–Female":"1482–Verstorben","11 January 1508":"11. Januar 1508","1575":"1575","1550":"1550","1482":"1482","1508":"1508","1480":"1480","Of Wortham, Suffolk, England":"Wortham, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom","Wortham, Suffolk, England":"Wortham, Suffolk, England","lifeSummary":"Mary Wright wurde 1482 in Wortham, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom geboren. Sie hatte mit John Betts mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"1482–